    <div class="gk-tip">
      <strong>Quick orientation:</strong> AEC founded <strong>1948</strong>; DAE founded <strong>1954</strong> (under PM). Three-stage programme conceived by <strong>Homi J. Bhabha (1954)</strong> — Stage 1 PHWRs → Stage 2 FBRs → Stage 3 Thorium reactors. India has the world's <strong>largest thorium reserves</strong> (~25% of global). Operational nuclear capacity: <strong>~8,880 MW</strong> (25 reactors, ~3% of electricity). Nuclear doctrine: <strong>No First Use + Credible Minimum Deterrence</strong>. India is NOT a signatory to NPT or CTBT.
    </div>

